  "contenu": [
    {
      "id": "2c1ac6b4-f03b-4e0e-ad1e-9ff6f33de539",
      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soit $A = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 & 1 \\\\ -1 & 0 & 2 \\\\ 0 & 1 & -1 \\end{pmatrix} \\in \\mathcal{M}_{3}(\\mathbb{R})$.",
        "html": "<p>Soit <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 &amp; 0 &amp;\n1 \\\\ -1 &amp; 0 &amp; 2 \\\\ 0 &amp; 1 &amp; -1 \\end{pmatrix} \\in\n\\mathcal{M}_{3}(\\mathbb{R})\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "4768c101-82c7-4353-a0bd-fb30ac40426a",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Calculer le déterminant de $A$.",
        "html": "<p>Calculer le déterminant de <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(A\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "844b59ec-80bf-4210-8487-6557651c9b0a",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "On développe $A$ suivant la 2ème colonne pour obtenir:\\\\\n $$\\det(A)=-1 \\times (2\\times 1-1 \\times (-1))=-3.$$",
        "html": "<p>On développe <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A\\)</span> suivant la 2ème\ncolonne pour obtenir:<br />\n<span class=\"math display\">\\[\\det(A)=-1 \\times (2\\times 1-1 \\times\n(-1))=-3.\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "c3bab3df-217a-430b-bbba-8490dd8d0422",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $A^3-3A +3I_{3}$ est la matrice nulle.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A^3-3A +3I_{3}\\)</span> est\nla matrice nulle.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "bf357d57-8758-468e-bf8d-7fae4aa2bd14",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$A^2=\\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 & 1 \\\\ -1 & 2 & -3 \\\\ -1 & -1 & 3 \\end{pmatrix}$\n    $A^3=\\begin{pmatrix} 0 & 0 & 3 \\\\ -3 & -3 & 6 \\\\ 0 & 3 & -6 \\end{pmatrix}$\n    d'o\\`u $A^3-3A=-3 I_{3} \\Longleftrightarrow A^3-3A+3 I_{3}=0$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(A^2=\\begin{pmatrix} 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 \\\\\n-1 &amp; 2 &amp; -3 \\\\ -1 &amp; -1 &amp; 3 \\end{pmatrix}\\)</span> <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(A^3=\\begin{pmatrix} 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 3 \\\\ -3 &amp;\n-3 &amp; 6 \\\\ 0 &amp; 3 &amp; -6 \\end{pmatrix}\\)</span> d’où <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(A^3-3A=-3 I_{3} \\Longleftrightarrow A^3-3A+3\nI_{3}=0\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "67c7a67c-a72d-4181-917b-453c65451726",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Déduire d'une des questions précédentes que $A$ est inversible et déterminer son inverse.",
        "html": "<p>Déduire d’une des questions précédentes que <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(A\\)</span> est inversible et déterminer son\ninverse.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "63fd566d-db22-4543-bfb5-8c8166d3fbb6",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "On a donc $A \\times \\frac{1}{-3}(A^2-3 I_{3})=I_{3}$ et la matrice inverse est donc\n$A^{-1}= -\\frac{1}{3}(A^2-3 I_{3})$",
        "html": "<p>On a donc <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A \\times \\frac{1}{-3}(A^2-3\nI_{3})=I_{3}\\)</span> et la matrice inverse est donc <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(A^{-1}= -\\frac{1}{3}(A^2-3 I_{3})\\)</span></p>\n"
      }
    }
  ],
